metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #264
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Beautiful M1nds #114
metadata.description:
This project is dedicated to the beautiful minds of the last centuries. I am talking about philosophy, math, science, physics, everything related to human knowledge.

I chosen 6 illustrious thinkers: Karl Marx, Stephen Hawking, Albert Einstein, Nikola Tesla, Sigmund Freud and Alan Turing. Each one of them made the world to step forward on different perspectives.

The algorithm is creating the famous iconic shapes of the beautiful minds using only letters, and the letters are just taken from their own books:
Karl Marx - Das Kapital
Sigmund Freud - The Interpretation of Dreams
Stephen Hawking - Particle Creation by Black Holes
Nikola Tesla - The Inventions Researches and Writings
Albert Einstein - Relativity
Alan Turing - Computing Machinery and Intelligence

There are 3 features:
The Font
The Size of the Font
The Author

The smaller is the font size, the more accurate becomes the image.
This is a tribute to human knowledge but also to Visual Poetry Art or Data Poetry and phenomenal artists like Jiri Kolar.

metadata.name: Color of life #44
metadata.description:
console.log("Hello world")

After many thoughts about life, about our relationship as individuals in a society I always bring myself the same doubt, does life become only what we do? Or can we, humans, be personalities without being defined by our professions?

This piece comes from this reflection, when I say that I work with art made with code they soon think that I am an unemployed bum. This work represents the colors that in round and elongated shapes abstract my relationship between code and art, putting beauty in continuous lines, and many times confusing in a general context.

PS: Press [S] to save a png :)

Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.
